<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-02T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/282: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-02T19:00:00+01:00">March
                                        2, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received March 2—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>66. Your No. 17, February 27, noon. Suvich<note n="45" xml:id="d479fn45">Fulvio Suvich, Italian Minister for Foreign
                                    Affairs.</note> expresses real interest in the subject. He is
                                uninformed as to financial ability but will discuss with the
                                Minister of Finance, the Foreign Exchange Control and Mussolini and
                                will talk to me in a few days. He says they have no understanding
                                with England or France and it is preferable that those Governments
                                be not advised that the matter is even being considered.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>